def ocr_node.OCR.get_hsv (   self,

)

for detecting marker, we pre-process image to hsv.

the function return h, s, v image. for detecting marker, we're gonna use h image cause color of marker is yellow and it's opposite of micropipette body color(body color is indigo)

Parameters
[in]imgdraft_roi_img should be input
Note
input constraints:
- image should not be empty
- image should be color image (3 channel)
output constraints:
- h_image should not be empty
- h_image should be mono image (1 channel)
- s_image should not be empty
- s_image should be mono image (1 channel)
- v_image should not be empty
- v_image should be mono image (1 channel)
Returns
h_img, s_img, v_img: all images sould be return

)

for rgb or hsv image we could adapt inrange function in opencv

Parameters
[in]imginput image. it should be color image.
[in]min1the first min parameter.
[in]min2the second min parameter.
[in]min3the thirds min parameter.
[in]max1the first max parameter.
[in]max2the second max parameter.
[in]max3the thirds max parameter.
Note
input constraints:
- image should not be empty
- image should be color image (3 channel)
- all min~max values should be ranged in 0~255
output constraints:
- ranged_img should not be empty
- ranged_img should be binary image (1 channel)
Returns
ranged_img: output ranged image.

Definition at line 822 of file ocr_node.py.

◆ get_semantic_image()

def ocr_node.OCR.get_semantic_image (   self,
  img,
  each_roi_pts,
  bounding_rect_list,
  rt_vol_list,
  valid_vol 
)

draw semantic image for debugging.

it has marker roi image which which has bounding rectangle for each digit of volume indicator.
there are also information like real-time volum / valid volume
real-time volume is estimated volume at every time. even though all the digits are not detected successfully.
valid volume is calculated real-time value. when the digits are detected successfully, we append this volume to list. and

Parameters
[in]imginput image. it should be roi image maden with marker
Note
input constraints:
- image should not be empty
- image should be color image (3 channel)
output constraints:
- semantic_img should not be empty
- semantic_img should be color image (3 channel)
Returns
semantic_img: output semantic image.

◆ get_valid_volume()

def ocr_node.OCR.get_valid_volume (   self,
  rt_vol,
  max_param = 5 
)

we calculate valid volume with max function.

the method is simple. we append real-time volume to list and if the list is bigger than max_param then it will get max volume.

Parameters
[in]rt_volreal-time volume
[in]vol_listvolume list, it is member variable
[in]max_paramit would decide the volumes of list is valid
Note
input constraints:
- rt_vol should be ranged 0~100
- vol_list should not be over max_param
output constraints:
- valid_vol should be ranged 0~100
Returns
valid_vol: valid volume
